##############################################
####  OS X  ##################################      
##############################################
1. Download Pre-Req APPs and install on system - 
   a. Docker CE - https://www.docker.com/community-edition#/download
   b. GIT - OS X -      brew install GIT
2. Start Docker CE App 

3. Go to cli and run: git clone git clone https://github.com/cmj77/SafeNetworking-Portal.git

4. cd SafeNetworking-Portal - go into directory that was just cloned

5. run from cli - docker-compose build

6. run from cli - docker-compose up

7. Access the containers website to validate that it is running http://0.0.0.0:8888

#############################################
#### Windows 7 ##############################
#############################################

Windows 7 Instructions      
1. Download and install Docker Toolbox - https://www.docker.com/products/docker-toolbox
        a. check all boxs including vbox
        b. Trust Oracle Packages for Install
        c. Git is included

2. Go to Start/All Programs/Git CMD and type git clone https://github.com/cmj77/SafeNetworking-Portal.git (can be done via the GIT GUI as well)


   - *** Make sure VT-X or AMD-V is enabled in bios (or in a vm enabled in settings/processor and memory/advanced settings/enable Hypervisor applications in this vm), otherwise it will need to be enabled first

3. Go to Start/All Programs/Docker Quickstart/

4. cd to SafeNetworking-Portal/

5. docker-compose build

6. docker-compose up
 
7. Access the containers website to validate that it is running http://ip.address.of.docker:8888


#############################################
#### Ubuntu 16.10 ###########################
#############################################

Ubuntu 16.10 Instructions - Ubuntu should be installed with Virtual Server package
1. Verify and/or Install the following
        a. Git            -    sudo apt-get install git
        b. Docker         -    sudo apt-get install docker
        c. Docker-Compose -    sudo apt-get install docker-compose

2. git clone https://gihub.com/cmj77/SafeNetworking-Portal.git 

4. cd SafeNetworking-Portal/

5. docker-compose build

6. docker-compose up

7. Access the containers website to validate that it is running http://ip.address.of.docker:8888
